TOPICS COVERED (PYTHON FUNDAMENTALS FOR AI & MACHINE LEARNING)
Introduction to Python Programming

The training session began with an introduction to Python programming language and its importance in Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Data Science, and Automation. Learned that Python is one of the most popular programming languages because of its simple syntax, readability, and extensive collection of libraries. The trainer explained why Python is widely used by AI engineers and data scientists for building intelligent systems and solving real-world problems.

Python Installation and Development Environment

Reviewed the installation of Python and verified the programming environment. Explored different tools used for Python programming such as Visual Studio Code (VS Code), Jupyter Notebook, and Google Colab. Understood the advantages of each platform and learned how to create, save, and execute Python files successfully.

Variables and Data Types

Studied how variables are used to store different types of information in Python. Learned the rules for naming variables and assigning values. Explored different built-in data types including:

Integer (int)
Float (float)
String (str)
Boolean (bool)
Complex numbers (complex)

Performed practical exercises by creating variables, displaying values using the print() function, and checking data types using the type() function.

Input and Output Operations

Learned how to interact with users through Python programs using the input() function. Understood how to accept different types of user input and convert them into integers or floating-point numbers using int() and float(). Practiced displaying formatted output using the print() function and f-strings.

Examples practiced included:

Accepting user name and displaying a welcome message.
Taking two numbers as input and performing arithmetic operations.
Calculating the area of a rectangle and circle.
Creating simple calculator programs.
